      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LONDON TO A BRICK (7) was first up for more than three months when he came from this barrier for a 3.6m third at this venue. Should be better for that and has a decent record at this longer distance so has winning claims. CONSTANTINOPLE (8) scored back-to-back wins here in April and was good last start when he led from this barrier and fought well to go under by head. All of those were at the mile but he also owns a good strike rate at this longer distance. Big chance. WATTS UP PARTYTIME (6) has been a bit off his game of late but he has some big wins on his resume and did beat CONSTANTINOPLE when scoring at this circuit and distance earlier in his campaign. SPEEDY LOVER (4) wasn't too far from the placegetters last start and may be better suited up in distance having won over the trip three back. BENNIE AND THE JETS NZ (2) brings some good form from Victoria and draws to be competitive.",
